  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pick the <strong>coriander</strong> leaves from their stalks&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Chop the stalks finely, keep the leaves separate&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-beef-meatball-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>beef mince</strong>, <strong>fish sauce</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong><strong> garlic</strong> and <strong>coriander stalks</strong> (reserve the leaves for later!) to a medium bowl&nbsp;and mix thoroughly until combined (use clean hands!)</p>\r\n<p>Divide the beef mixture into 10 <span class=\"text-danger\">[20]</span> and shape into <strong>meatballs</strong></p>\r\n<p>Refrigerate the mixture until later&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-beef-meatball-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>carrot</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span>, then continue&nbsp;to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot 'ribbons'</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>cucumber&nbsp;</strong>into rounds, then slice the disks into matchsticks&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Shred the<strong> little gem lettuce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-beef-meatball-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the chilled <strong>meatballs</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cover with a lid and cook for 4-6 min, shaking occasionally so that the <strong>meatballs</strong> cook evenly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-beef-meatball-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and slice the <strong>shallot</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> finely</p>\r\n<p>Chop the<strong> roasted</strong>&nbsp;<strong>peanuts</strong> roughly</p>\r\n<p>Roll the <strong>lime</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice!) and cut into wedges&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-beef-meatball-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the cooked <strong>meatballs</strong> to a plate - leave the cooking juices in the pan&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>shallot</strong> to the pan and cook over a medium heat for 1 min or until warmed through but not softened</p>\r\n<p>Remove the pan from the heat and add the<strong> soy sauce</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Squeeze the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span>&nbsp;<strong>lime</strong> into the pan and mix&nbsp;- this is your<strong> shallot&nbsp;</strong><strong>dressing</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-beef-meatball-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>shredded little gem lettuce</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>cucumber </strong><strong>matchsticks</strong> and&nbsp;<strong>carrot ribbons</strong>&nbsp;to a large bowl</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>shallot dressing</strong> and mix with cleans hands - this is your <strong>salad</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-beef-meatball-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> meatballs</strong> over the salad and garnish with the reserved<strong> coriander leaves</strong>,&nbsp;<strong><strong>chopped</strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>peanuts</strong> and a wedge of<strong> lime</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
